# Project Idea - Banana Ripeness Detector

**Project Overview**
Use Edge Impulse to train an image classification model that can recognise four stages of banana ripeness (unripe / under_ripe / ripe / overripe). The model will be deployed on an Android phone, using the camera to detect ripeness in real time and give simple suggestions (e.g. “Ripe → eat it today!”).

**Techniques to use**

* Image classification (transfer learning with MobileNetV2)
* Edge Impulse Studio (end-to-end TensorFlow pipeline)
* Mobile phone camera as the sensor
* QR code deployment (run directly in the browser, no app needed)

**Data**
Images from the internet + my own photos (different lighting conditions, angles, and backgrounds)
4 classes, with a target of 300–500 images per class

**Label Definitions (Class)**
| Label      | Chinese Name | Description                                            |
| ---------- | ------------ | ------------------------------------------------------ |
| unripe     | Unripe       | Mostly green, clearly not ready to eat                 |
| under_ripe | Semi-ripe    | Starting to turn yellow, but not fully ready to eat    |
| ripe       | Ripe         | Mostly yellow, suitable for eating                     |
| overripe   | Overripe     | Many dark spots, softer texture, past optimal ripeness |


**Hardware**
Android phone (mobile phone, allowed for the course)

**Why this project**
Simple and practical, and it demonstrates the full pipeline from data collection to training and deployment. It also aligns with the concept of edge AI discussed in L6.
